ands</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step2"><label>Position patient in comfortable position , arranging support for area to be bandaged</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step3"><label>Provide privacy</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step4"><label>Ensure that skin and or dressing is clean and dry</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step5"><label>Separate any adjacent skin surface</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step6"><label>Align part to be bandaged , providing slight flexion if appropriate and not contraindicated</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step7"><label>Apply bandage from distal to proximal part</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step8"><label>Apply bandage with even distribution of pressure</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step9"><label>Use proper bandage turns 
- Circular 
- Apply bandage so that each round overlaps the previous turn 
- Secure in place 

- Spiral
- Make 2 circular turns 
- Continue so that each round of bandage slightly overlaps the previous round by about two thirds , progressing up the limb 
- End with 2 circular turns and secure with pins , tape or clips 

- Spiral reverse
- Make 2 circular turns
- Bring bandage upwards at 30 degree angle
- Place thumb of free hand on upper edge of bandage 
- Fold bandage back on itslelf
- Perform reversal of bandage at same spot on each turn 
- End with two circular turns and secure with safety pins 
- Figure of eight 
- Make two circular turns 
- Carry bandage above joint , around it , then below joint and around it
- Continue above and below joint making 2 circular turns
- End bandage above joint and circulation of extremity</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step10"><label>Assess tension of bandage and circulation of extremity</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step11"><label>Assess tension of bandage and circulation of extremity</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step12"><label>Document procedure</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1></group></h:body></h:html>